sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Container
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter<br/>(triton/mlserver/ovms/torchserve)<br/>8085/TCP gRPC
    participant Puller as Pullman Storage<br/>Framework
    participant Storage as Cloud Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>/models/
    participant Runtime as Inference Runtime<br/>(Triton/MLServer/OVMS/TS)

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 1: Model Load (Triton Example)

    MM->>Adapter: LoadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC/8085 localhost plaintext
    activate Adapter

    Adapter->>Puller: Pull model artifacts<br/>(embedded or standalone)
    activate Puller

    Puller->>Storage: GET model files<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Access Key / Service Account
    Storage-->>Puller: Model artifacts (binary data)
    Puller->>FS: Write model files to disk<br/>/models/_triton_models/{modelId}/

    deactivate Puller

    Note over Adapter,FS: Create Triton model layout:<br/>versioned dir + config.pbtxt + symlinks

    Adapter->>Runtime: RepositoryModelLoad(modelName)<br/>gRPC/8001 localhost plaintext
    activate Runtime
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Load success + model metadata
    deactivate Runtime

    Adapter-->>MM: LoadModel response<br/>(sizeInBytes, maxConcurrency)
    deactivate Adapter

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 2: Model Load (OVMS with Batch Processing)

    MM->>Adapter: LoadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC/8085 localhost plaintext
    activate Adapter

    Adapter->>Puller: Pull model artifacts
    Puller->>Storage: GET model files<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Storage-->>Puller: Model artifacts
    Puller->>FS: Write model files

    Note over Adapter: Batch accumulation<br/>100ms min - 3s max wait<br/>(actor pattern)

    Adapter->>Runtime: POST /v1/config/reload<br/>HTTP/8001 localhost plaintext
    activate Runtime
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Reload success (all batched models)
    deactivate Runtime

    Adapter-->>MM: LoadModel response
    deactivate Adapter

    Note over MM,Runtime: Flow 3: Keras Model Conversion (Triton)

    MM->>Adapter: LoadModel(.h5 Keras model)<br/>gRPC/8085 localhost
    activate Adapter

    Adapter->>Puller: Pull .h5 model file
    Puller->>Storage: GET .h5 file<br/>HTTPS/443
    Storage-->>Puller: Keras .h5 model
    Puller->>FS: Write .h5 to disk

    Note over Adapter: Detect .h5 format<br/>→ invoke tf_pb.py subprocess

    Adapter->>FS: subprocess: tf_pb.py<br/>Read .h5 → Write SavedModel/

    Adapter->>Runtime: RepositoryModelLoad(converted)<br/>gRPC/8001 localhost
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Load success

    Adapter-->>MM: LoadModel response
    deactivate Adapter

    Note over MM,Runtime: Model Unload

    MM->>Adapter: UnloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC/8085 localhost
    activate Adapter
    Adapter->>Runtime: RepositoryModelUnload / UnregisterModel<br/>gRPC or HTTP localhost
    Runtime-->>Adapter: Unload success
    Adapter->>FS: Clean up model files + symlinks
    Adapter-->>MM: UnloadModel response
    deactivate Adapter
